      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a really hard time sleeping lately. like i can barely stay asleep for more than a couple hours. i already take melatonin every night but it doesnt really seem to be doing much anymore. my doctor gave me some Ambien (zolpidem) to try out, but i was wondering if it's okay if i take the melatonin and the Ambien at the same time? i feel like if i combine them it might actually work better so i can finally get a full night. is that safe?",
